  "title": "Developmental Dysplasia of the Hip - Ultrasound",
  "source": "ddh-ultrasound.html",
  "blocks": [
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 2,
      "text": "Screening roadmap"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Summarized from Radiology Assistant guidance."
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 2,
      "text": "Risk factors"
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "items": [
        "Breech presentation (especially female).",
        "Positive family history of DDH.",
        "Oligohydramnios, first-born, swaddling with hips extended.",
        "Foot deformities or torticollis."
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 2,
      "text": "Technique & landmarks"
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "items": [
        "Coronal neutral view with lateral decubitus positioning; iliac wing horizontal.",
        "Landmarks: straight iliac line, bony acetabular roof, labrum, femoral head center.",
        "Alpha angle: bony roof; Beta angle: cartilaginous roof/labrum.",
        "Document stability with gentle stress (Barlow/Ortolani) if indicated."
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 2,
      "text": "Measurement tips"
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "items": [
        "Alpha >= 60 deg is normal (Graf I).",
        "Beta <= 55 deg typical for stable hips; higher values suggest poor coverage.",
        "Ensure the lower limb of the ileum is parallel to the probe to avoid false low alpha.",
        "Use the same neutral view for all measurements; avoid flexion/extension changes."
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 2,
      "text": "Graf classification (summary)"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 2,
      "text": "Reporting checklist"
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "items": [
        "Side(s), patient age, and risk factor indication.",
        "Technique: neutral coronal view, stress maneuvers performed or not.",
        "Alpha/Beta angles for each hip; Graf type; stability (Barlow/Ortolani response).",
        "Femoral head coverage/cartilage roof appearance; labrum morphology.",
        "Recommendation: follow-up interval or treatment (e.g., Pavlik harness), radiograph if ossified."
      ]
    },
